snippet.textDisplay:
I would challenge the educated/reasonable* "anti-vaxxers" (or however they identify) 
to consider that there is always compromise in any non primitive society. You can't go into any safe nightclub and demand drinks etc without showing I.D, then paying for drinks etc. And shockingly....you can't enter a country (during a pandemic) and potentially spread infection (when hospitals are already at capacity) and take prize money (likley paid by law abiding tax payers - when many are financially stuggling) without following the stated rules. Rules are rules; rarely are they accepted by everyone) but they are usually better for society; often the elite are above them (Trump making a laughing stock of USA with his immunity to sooooo many rules!) but less so (look at Prince Andrew). Go Australia 🇦🇺 for setting a good example. 
 
On a personal level, Djokavich displays a temperamentality that makes him a poor role model and this type of victim hood is really immature. If I go to a nightclub without I.D, I go home. If my dodgy bouncer says "I can probably sneak you in" then that's the risk I take (if I still get asked to leave). Just come back next time following the rules or find a new place to go Novak. The Australian Open will be enjoyed by reasonable tennis fans but we'd have liked you to play, of course. C'est la vie.

*the unreasonable are beyond any discussion at times and repeat the same  arguments due to the kruger dunning effect (which is worth using as a tool to educate their misconception that  "I actually know something about a topic (e.g vaccines are bad!) and so I am as qualified as the experts (scientists, doctors...), as I don't realise that they know more").
